Finally, there are here and there, especially towards the end of the play, some corrections and remarks written in black ink in a hand strongly resembling that of Camerarius, and which have been ascribed to him: Thus, in Ι. iii. 93, which appears in B,

illulz'er quese suamq etalem spernit speculo elusa est,

where the a in elusa is written over an erasure, we find in the margin in the hand spoken of, ei usus est. These notes, by whomsoever written, are evidently modern, and may be safely neglected by any collator, however scrupulous.
